channel.title: [HELP] I aint too nooby at this
channel.description:
Ok, i got all everything together, all the right programs all the java coding and classpaths, no-ip server..all those goodies, BUT whenever i try to run my server i get this
Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details
ANYONE know what that is?

item.title: [HELP] I aint too nooby at this
item.dc:creator: @uncfan1119 uncfan1119
item.description:
@uncfan1119 wrote:

Hey buddy, I remeberd you need to do this, I even tested it myself! Copy and paste this new code in their!

@echo on
COLOR 08
title YOURSERVERNAME Client
javac -Xlint:deprecation Applet5.java

“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_06\bin\javac.exe” -cp . *.java
“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.5.0_06\bin\java.exe” server
pause

[br][size=1]Posted at: September 10, 2006, 08:15:20 AM[/size][hr]Now it should run the thingy I found was the javac -Xlint:deprecation Applet5.java, hopefully you will be on aim.
[br][size=1]Posted at: September 10, 2006, 08:15:57 AM[/size][hr]Don’t forget to change the javajdk.1.5.0_6 to javajdk.1.5.0_7
